  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Coordinate and work closely with Project Manager to oversee site matters and provide technical support such as interpret construction drawings</li><li>Ensure all technical drawings conform to the latest BCA codes and regulations</li><li>Supervise site progress and ensure timely delivery of contract works from subcontractors/suppliers</li><li>Manage subcontractors/suppliers to perform their respective scope of works for smooth project execution</li><li>Conduct regular site inspections and enforce in-house regulations</li><li>Attend site meetings to assist the Project Manager with necessary preparatory works and coordination with consultants</li><li>Liaise with relevant government agencies to obtain necessary site permits/clearances</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as instructed by superiors</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Qualifications / Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Possess a recognised Degree or Diploma in Architecture / Civil / Structural / Mechanical / Electrical Engineering, Building Science, Building Management, Building Services Engineering, Construction Management and <strong>at least 3 years of relevant working experience</strong> of the building construction industry</li></ul><p>or</p><ul><li>Degree in local universities in Architecture / Civil / Structural / Mechanical / Electrical Engineering, Building Science, Building Management, Building Services Engineering, Construction Management</li><li>Strong knowledge in use of Autocad, BIM software such as Revit and microsoft projects</li></ul>",
